[SN]TITLE[SN]
FTSE 100 higher in early trade

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): The FTSE 100 made a positive start to the week, with shares in Royal Mail and M&S higher ahead of their results later this week.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The benchmark FTSE 100 index climbed 46.65 points to 7,007.14.
Shares in Royal Mail and Marks & Spencer both rose about 2%, with the two firms due to report full-year results later this week.
BHP Billiton was the biggest faller, down 4.7%, after shares in its spin-off, South32, began trading.
